{"article_id":"H9DdzlEjYQFcnoVW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"New York Times article says","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"competing storylines about 2012 Benghazi attack likely are both wrong","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The report says","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"contrary to GOP assertions , al Qaeda was probably not involved in the attack","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The article suggests","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"independent Libyan militias played a key role instead","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Report :","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"Anti-Muslim video may have sparked the violence ,","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"but not solely ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"as suggested by Obama administration","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"A New York Times report on the September 11 , 2012 , attack","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"that killed four Americans","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"-- including Ambassador J. Christopher Stevens --","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"in Benghazi , Libya ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"calls into question much of what","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Republicans","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"accusing the Obama administration of a cover-up","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"have said about the incident .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"The three main points of contention have been","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"whether the attack was planned ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"whether it was sparked by an anti-Muslim video ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"and whether al Qaeda was involved .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"However ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"the Times says ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"the administration 's version ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"focusing on outrage over the inflammatory video ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"and first delivered by then-ambassador to the U.N. Susan Rice on Sunday morning talk shows five days later ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"is n't exactly right , either .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"`` The reality in Benghazi was different , and murkier ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"than either of those story lines suggests .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Benghazi was not infiltrated by Al Qaeda ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"but nonetheless contained grave local threats to American interests .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"The attack does not appear to have been meticulously planned ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"but neither was it spontaneous or without warning signs , ''","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"according to David D. Kirkpatrick 's article in the Times .","depth":4},{"id":36,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"GOP leaders dispute new Benghazi report","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"GOP leaders dispute new Benghazi report","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"02:24","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"It 's a conclusion","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"that CNN has drawn in its previous reporting .","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"The attack at the Benghazi diplomatic compound has become a political flashpoint in a long-running battle between the White House and Republicans ,","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"who accuse the Obama administration of not bolstering security before the attack ,","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"of botching the response to it","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"and of misleading the public for political gain less than two months before the November election .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"The GOP suggests","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"the administration removed specific terror references","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"and stuck to the explanation","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"advanced by Rice","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"-- later proved untrue --","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that the attack was the result of spontaneous demonstrations over the U.S.-produced film `` Innocence of Muslims , ''","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"which contained scenes","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"some Muslims considered blasphemous .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"The White House and its allies in Congress have said","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"any confusion and conflicting information in the early hours and days after the assault stemmed from the `` fog of war , ''","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"not any deliberate effort","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"to mislead the public .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"The White House had no comment","depth":4},{"id":61,"text":"when CNN requested a response to the Times article .","depth":4},{"id":62,"text":"After reading it ,","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"Obama 's former national security spokesman Tommy Vietor unleashed a series of tweets ,","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"including these ,","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"condemning Republicans","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"who 've spent more than a year","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"lambasting and investigating the Beghazi incident :","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"-- `` If Rs spent 1/50th as much time as @ ddknyt","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"learning what really happened in # Benhazi ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"we could have avoided months of disgusting demagoguery . ''","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"-- `` Republicans inflated the role of al Qaeda in # Bengazi","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"to attack Obama 's CT record .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"They were wrong ,","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"and handed our enemy a propaganda win . ''","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"-- `` Credit to @ ddknyt","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"but also disconcerting that his # Benghazi article offered more insight into what happened than all Congressional hearings . ''","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"The Times ' article ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"which includes interviews with several Libyan militia leaders","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"who helped bring down Col. Moammar Gadhafi 's dictatorship in 2012 ,","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"says","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"no evidence supports speculation about al Qaeda 's involvement in the Benghazi attack .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"To the contrary , the Times reports","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"that the diverse and fractured opposition militias ,","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"many of whom were at least somewhat friendly toward U.S. interests ,","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"most likely contributed to the attack .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"That dovetails with the findings of the State Department investigative panel report on Benghazi .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"`` The Benghazi attacks also took place in a context","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"in which the global terrorism threat","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"as most often represented by al Qaeda","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"( AQ )","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"is fragmenting and increasingly devolving to local affiliates and other actors","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"who share many of AQ 's aims ,","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"including violent anti-Americanism ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"without necessarily being organized or operated under direct AQ command and control , ''","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"the report said .","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"The Times report zeroes in on militia leader Abu Khattala as well as the like-minded Islamist militia Ansar al Sharia .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"In a recent interview with CNN 's Arwa Damon , Khattala acknowledged","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"being at the Benghazi mission after the attack","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"but denied any involvement .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"Damon spent two hours interviewing Khattala at a coffee shop at a well-known hotel in Benghazi .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"He allowed Damon to use an audio recorder","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"to tape the conversation ,","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"but refused to appear on camera .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Khattala 's narrative of the events that night was sometimes unclear","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"and , at times , seemed to be contradictory ,","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"Damon said .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"He admitted to being at the compound the night of the attack ,","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"but denied any involvement in the violence .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"Asked about allegations","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"he may have masterminded the attack ,","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"Khattala and two of the men","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"he brought with him to the interview","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"`` burst out","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"laughing , ''","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"Damon said .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"Khattala told CNN","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"that he had not been questioned by either Libyan authorities or the FBI .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"The militia leader was one of those","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"whom U.S. prosecutors charged in the attacks ,","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"as CNN first reported","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"Ansar al Sharia is more a label than an organization , one","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"that 's been adopted by conservative Salafist groups across the Arab world .","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"The name means , simply , `` Partisans of Islamic Law . ''","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"In Benghazi , Ansar al Sharia was one of many groups","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"that filled the vacuum of authority","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"following the overthrow of Gadhafi .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"The group 's central belief is that all authority is derived from the Prophet Mohammed ,","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"that democracy is un-Islamic","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"and that other branches of Islam , such as the Sufi , are heretical .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"There do not appear to be organizational links between Ansar al Sharia and al Qaeda ,","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"but there is solidarity .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"Among the group 's Benghazi membership is Mohammed al-Zahawi ,","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"who fought to overthrow Gadhafi","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"and praised al Qaeda leader Ayman al Zawahiri in a BBC interview .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"al Qaeda 's statements `` help galvanize the Muslim nation ,","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"maintain its dignity and pride . ''","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"A different Ansar al Sharia is affiliated with al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula in Yemen ,","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"and budding franchises are said to exist in Tunisia , Morocco and Egypt .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":279,"left":175,"right":278,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":150,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":146,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":0,"right":145,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":145,"left":141,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":144,"left":142,"right":143,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":142,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":143,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":7,"right":148,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":8,"right":147,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":167,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":161,"right":166,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":161,"left":157,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":153,"right":156,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":152,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":15